# Implementation Plan - UI Layout Adjustments

## Goal
Optimize the UI layout of the "Real-time Monitoring Map" section by reducing the prominence of secondary action buttons (excessively large) and ensuring the map title is clearly visible.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Style Adjustments ([style.css](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/style.css))
- **Add `.glass-btn.small` modifier**:
  - Reduce padding to `6px 12px` (from `8px 16px`).
  - Reduce font size to `0.75rem` (from `0.8rem`).
  - Adjust icon gap if necessary.

### 2. HTML Structure ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/index.html))
- **Apply `.small` class**:
  - Update `export-csv-btn` and `print-btn` to include the new `.small` modifier.
- **Verify Map Title**:
  - Ensure the `<h2>` for "リアルタイム監視マップ" is correctly styled (check strictness of existing CSS) and clearly legible.

## Verification
- User to verify visually that the buttons are less obtrusive and the map title remains clear.
